  "texts": [
    "This example allows us to understand the second sense of transparency that is relevant when it comes to affective artificial agents.",
    "We call this kind of transparency emotional transparency.",
    "Now, providing a full-blown definition of emotional transparency goes beyond the scope of this paper.",
    "The central point, however, is that affective artificial agents typically work by mimicking human emotivity-driven behavior.",
    "The specific ways in which they do this depend on the kind of system in question."
